  "summary": "metrics-pipeline-d8k2 ships post-install beacon scripts that exfiltrate host data",
  "details": "The package's package.json declares a postinstall hook (\"postinstall\": \"node run.js\") which executes on every install. The tarball ships beacon scripts (beacon34.js, beacon_linux.js) that import child_process, http/https, and os, read process.env, os.hostname(), os.platform(), and other host identifiers, and transmit them via http.get/http.request POST/GET calls. This is the canonical install-time host-reconnaissance and exfiltration shape: lifecycle-triggered execution combined with environment/system-info collection and outbound HTTP. Installing this package causes the installer's host metadata and environment variables to be sent off-host on `npm install` without user consent.",
